#week-title("Two", "Rainwater: The Secret Acid")

=== Core Teaching

The preparation of the Philosophic Mercury begins with the collection and
fermentation of rainwater. Through the long putrefaction in a sealed vessel, the
rainwater generates a "secret acid" — a subtle mineral solvent.

This week, perform the first distillation of your collected rainwater. Then, set
up a new fermentation in a sealed vessel to begin the generation of this
acid.

#lab[
  *Rainwater Protocol*
  + *Distillation:* Collect and distil your rainwater once to remove
    pollutants.
  + *Fermentation:* Place the distilled water in a large globe.
  + *Sealing:* Seal tightly and place in dark, moderate warmth.
  + *Observation:* Watch for the transition from clear to turbid.
]

=== Topics This Week

- Distilling rainwater for laboratory use
- Generating the secret acid through fermentation
- Sealed vessel vs. Breathing vessel: when to use each

#inner-work[
  *The Vessel of Mind*

  Contemplate your own mind as a "sealed vessel." Just as the water generates its
  acid when kept in darkness and warmth, your insights often generate when you
  withdraw from the noise of the world.

  Practice a daily 10-minute "Silence of the Vessel" meditation — no intake of
  information, no output of thought, only internal warmth.
]

